Hello Norrathians<br>
<br>
I'm organizing a rally across Norrath that will take place on thursday, may 29th, 9pm EST. The rally is a race where participants have to solve different riddles to move forward. Here are the basic rules:<br>
<br>
1- To participate, you can be of any race but can only be a non-gating class: warrior, ranger, paladin, rogue, shadowknight, beastlord or monk. Other classes are allowed to help participants. Also, participants should be at least level 25 or higher but it is not required.<br>
<br>
2- The expansions required to participate are: Kunark, Luclin and PoP<br>
<br>
3- It will cost 200pp per participant. Any participant may (and should) hire a crew to help him but through every step, rally items will only be handed to registered participants.<br>
<br>
4- The first participant to complete the rally will win 30 000 gold pieces (3k pp)<br>
<br>
5- No tradeskills are necessary to participate but it'd be useful to have 30ish skill points in one of them at one point. No special abilities such as tracking, hiding and sneaking are needed. Sow, horses and all other ways to travel fast should be used for obvious reasons.<br>
<br>
6- At least 10 participants (or teams) are needed for rally to take place.<br>
<br>
7- The maximum time allowed to complete the rally is 4 hours (real time). If no participants has completed the rally after that time, all participants will get their money back.<br>
<br>
If you feel like competing in a whole different way and want to test your knowledge of the world of Norrath, this is your chance!<br>
<br>
To register or if you have questions, simply send me a tell in game or send me an email at louduchemin@yahoo.com. I won't accept money before the event.<br>
<br>
Gaex Mahaar, ranger of Karana, 50th spring  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=melediweaver>melediweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dirges, a specialty</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/20/03 2:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Great Norrath Rally</span><hr size=1> Just curious, are non gating Bards allowed in? <p><img border=0 src="http://home.golden.net/~effinger/sig.jpg" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=louduc>louduc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/20/03 4:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Great Norrath Rally</span><hr size=1> Yes, bards are allowed... sorry i forgot to mention them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
